msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.223:0.2"
msgid "23. Duccaritavagga "
msgstr "23. Bad Conduct "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.223:0.3"
msgid "223. Akataññutāsutta "
msgstr "223. Ungrateful "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.229, sc1
msgctxt "an4.223:1.1"
msgid "“Catūhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bālo abyatto asappuriso khataṃ upahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati, sāvajjo ca hoti sānuvajjo viññūnaṃ, bahuñca apuññaṃ pasavati. "
msgstr "“When a foolish, incompetent bad person has four qualities they keep themselves broken and damaged. They deserve to be blamed and criticized by sensible people, and they make much bad karma. "

msgctxt "an4.223:1.2"
msgid "Katamehi catūhi? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "an4.223:1.3"
msgid "Kāyaduccaritena, vacīduccaritena, manoduccaritena, akataññutā akataveditā—"
msgstr "Bad conduct by way of body, speech, and mind, and being ungrateful and thankless. "

msgctxt "an4.223:1.4"
msgid "imehi … pe … kāyasucaritena, vacīsucaritena, manosucaritena kataññutākataveditā … pe …. "
msgstr "An astute person … makes much merit. … Good conduct by way of body, speech, and mind, and being grateful and thankful. …” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.223:1.5"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

